<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
    <!--
        GameActivity extends androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity, so the
        activity theme must inherit from Theme.AppCompat.* (the platform
        Theme.NoTitleBar.Fullscreen isn't compatible — it crashes in
        AppCompatDelegateImpl.createSubDecor with "You need to use a
        Theme.AppCompat theme (or descendant) with this activity").

        The action bar is hidden via the parent theme. Edge-to-edge drawing
        is opted into imperatively from MainActivity.onCreate via
        WindowCompat.setDecorFitsSystemWindows(false) — we deliberately do
        NOT set android:windowFullscreen=true here, because that hides the
        status bar while leaving the framebuffer excluded from the nav-bar
        region, which makes GameActivity's SYSTEM_BARS insets report zero
        and the HUD has no way to know where to pull back from.

        With edge-to-edge on: framebuffer spans the whole display, insets
        are reported correctly for both bars, and bars remain visible so
        the user can still navigate system UI. A future "sticky immersive"
        mode can hide the bars via WindowInsetsControllerCompat.
    -->
    <style name="Theme.Uldum" parent="Theme.AppCompat.NoActionBar">
        <item name="android:windowContentOverlay">@null</item>
        <item name="android:windowActionBar">false</item>
    </style>
</resources>
